          <tr>
          <td align="left" valign="center">
          <font size="+1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#F52E00>
          <b>Connections</b>
          </font>
          </td>
          </tr>
          <tr><td colspan=2 height=1><img src=../../../img/blank.gif width=1 height=1></td></tr>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
        </table>
        <a name=conn_pwr></a>
        <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
          <tr>
          <td align="left" valign="center">
          <font size="+0" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#F52E00>
          Power
          </font>
          </td>
          </tr>
          <tr><td colspan=2 height=1><img src=../../../img/blank.gif width=1 height=1></td></tr>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
        </table>
        <table width=100% border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
          <tr>
          <td valign=top align=left>
          <font size="-1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#555555>
The power socket is located at the rear of the device, next to the two
serial ports. It is a regular power connector, but <font color=#F52E00>note</font> that the
(-) terminal is at the centre and the (+) terminal is the outer ring.
This is the other way around as with most European devices.
The power socket is not in&#173;tended for powering the device but rather for
charging the internal battery pack (8 hours max.).
<font color=#F52E00>Also note</font> that the battery is part of the power circuit. It <b>must</b> be
present for correct operation.
          </font>
          </td></tr>
        </table>
<br />        <table width=100% border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=4>
          <tr>
          <td valign="">
          <font size="-1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#555555>
          <ol>
            <li><div style="display:inline-block; width:60px;">GND</div>Ground (0V)            <li><div style="display:inline-block; width:60px;">PWR</div>+6V DC          </ol>
          </font>
          </td>
          <td>
          <font size="-1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#555555>
          <ol>
            <table 
             border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td align="center" valign=>
